         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">11/8/70. ¶  ¶ The case pr. Joshua, ¶  dear Mr Bentham, has safely arrived, and I am right glad to get thus gradually back my plants for the Museum. Occasions for comparison arise so often and the abse...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">70.08.11a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To George Bentham</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RBG Kew, Kew correspondence, Australia, Mueller, 1858-70, f. 445.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">11/8/70.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The case pr. Joshua,<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="color: #000000; ">That is, the clipper ship </seg>
                     <seg style="color: #000000; font-style: italic; ">J. M. Joshua</seg>
                     <seg style="color: #000000; font-style: italic; font-weight: bold; ">.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> dear Mr Bentham, has safely arrived, and I am right glad to get thus gradually back my plants for the Museum. Occasions for comparison arise so often and the absense of any large number of plants is sure to render one helpless. </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Like in <name key="Myrocarpus">Myrocarpus</name> so in certain Boroneae the aestivation is subject to aberrations.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">With best wishes</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Boronia">Boronia</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Myrocarpus">Myrocarpus</name>
            </p>
